Size segmentation in the ball valves market plays a crucial role in meeting diverse industrial needs. The preference for mid-sized ball valves ranging from 1” to 6” is poised to fuel market growth as these sizes are commonly used across various industries for flow control applications. Additionally, the versatility and reliability of stainless steel ball valves are driving their demand, especially in applications requiring corrosion resistance and durability. Stainless steel's favorable properties make it a preferred material choice, contributing to the growth of the market segment based on material. Manufacturers are focusing on developing advanced materials and coatings to enhance the performance and longevity of ball valves, thereby expanding their market presence and meeting customer demands for highly efficient and long-lasting products.

